In terms of organization size, IWMS vendors are targeting both Small and Medium-Sized Enterprises (SMEs) and Large Enterprises, offering tailored solutions to meet the specific requirements of each segment. SMEs are increasingly recognizing the benefits of IWMS in improving operational efficiency, optimizing resource utilization, and enhancing overall workplace productivity. Large enterprises, on the other hand, are leveraging IWMS to manage complex workplace environments, multiple locations, and diverse asset portfolios efficiently. The vertical segment includes industries such as Banking, Financial Services, and Insurance (BFSI), IT and Telecom, Retail and E-commerce, Healthcare, among others, where IWMS is being deployed to address sector-specific challenges and drive digital transformation. Industries such as BFSI and IT are at the forefront of IWMS adoption, driven by the need to enhance regulatory compliance, streamline operations, and optimize real estate portfolios.

